suites.title: Calculate the factorial of a given integer.
suites.description:
Factorial of a non-negative integer, is multiplication of all integers smaller than or equal to n.
For example factorial of 6 is 6 * 5 * 4 * 3 * 2 * 1 which is 720.

Factorial can be calculated iteratively or recursively. You can solve using any approach.

suites.title: Print a text message on the console.
suites.description:
The Hello World program is a program that prints "Hello, world!". It is very simple in most
programming languages, and is used to show the basic syntax of a programming language.

Write a program to print "Hello, world!" on the console.

Example run:
```
$ node index.js
Hello, world!‚èé
```
